'''''Steel Thunder''''' is a 1988 video game published by [[Accolade (company)|Accolade]]. Designed by Tom Loughry, it is labeled an "American Battle Tank Simulation" on the title screen.<ref name=lemon>{{lemon64 game|id=2476}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Steel Thunder'' is a game in which modern [[armored warfare]] is simulated.<ref name="CGW54"/>

==Reception==
Wyatt Lee reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "Accolade has: 1) paved the way for future tank simulations, 2) proven that the company is serious about developing more than action games, and 3) published a challenging game all in one bold stroke."<ref name="CGW54">{{cite magazine |last=Lee |first=Wyatt |title=Don't Tread On Me!: Accolade's "Steel Thunder" Modern Armor |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=December 1988 |volume=1 |issue=54 |pages=8â€“9}}</ref>

